CakePHP Facebook Plugin

A CakePHP Plugin used for interfacing with the Facebook PHP SDK.

For a full list of available methods and properties, please refer to the PHP SDK Overview here:

http://developers.facebook.com/docs/reference/php/

INSTALLATION
------------

1. Copy the plugin to app/Plugin/Facebook
2. Enable the plugin in app/Config/bootstrap.php

CONFIGURATION
---------------

In your controller:

    public $components = array(
        'Facebook.Facebook' => array(
            'appId' => YOUR_FACEBOOK_APP_ID,
            'appSecret' => YOUR_FACEBOOK_APP_SECRET
        ),
    );

    public $helpers = array(
        'Facebook.Facebook' => array(
            'appId' => YOUR_FACEBOOK_APP_ID,
            'appSecret' => YOUR_FACEBOOK_APP_SECRET
        ),
    );

You can also pass more configuration options as defaults. For example:

    public $helpers = array(
        'Facebook.Facebook' => array(
            'appId' => YOUR_FACEBOOK_APP_ID,
            'appSecret' => YOUR_FACEBOOK_APP_SECRET,
            'scope' => array(
                'email',
                'user_interests',
                'user_location',
            ),
        ),
    );

USAGE
---------------

The following example shows how to use the FacebookHelper::login method to
create a Facebook login link.

    echo $this->Facebook->login(__('Login with Facebook'), array(
        'redirect_uri' => '/',
        'scope' => array(
            'email',
            'user_interests',
            'user_location'
        )
    ));

NOTE: In the above example, if you've already specified the scope in you configuration options, you don't need to specify it here. For example:

    echo $this->Facebook->login(__('Login with Facebook'), array('redirect_uri' => '/'));

The following example shows how to use the FacebookHelper::logout method to
create a Facebook logout link.

    echo $this->Facebook->logout(__('Logout'), array(
        'next' => array(
            'controller' => 'users',
            'action' => 'logout'
        )
    ));

The following example shows how to use the FacebookComponent to check if the
user is logged in with Facebook and then get their data:

    if ($this->Facebook->loggedIn()) {
        $facebookUser = $this->Facebook->user();
    }
